OL,3,CMerseyside MPs join calls for a fairer
OL,4,Ccouncil tax system
OL,6,FIt's thought that with a proportional
OL,7,Fproperty tax, the average household
OL,8,Fcould save about #800 a year.
OL,10,FHomeowners would pay a flat percentage
OL,11,Fof their current property value, as
OL,12,Fwould landlords, while tenants would
OL,13,Fnot pay it.
OL,15,FThe chair of campaign group Fairer
OL,16,FShare Andrew Dixon says councils would
OL,17,Fnot lose much-needed revenue.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
